01:23:27,585 --> 01:23:30,504
I wasn't looking for them.
I thought they were on Edmund.

967
01:23:30,672 --> 01:23:33,966
- Where could they have gone?
- I don't know.

968
01:23:36,803 --> 01:23:38,303
- Betty.
- The housekeeper?

969
01:23:38,471 --> 01:23:40,472
Where would she have put them?
You've been through his things.

970
01:23:40,640 --> 01:23:41,807
She might have taken them.

971
01:23:41,975 --> 01:23:43,726
Listen to me. That's why I fired her.

972
01:23:43,893 --> 01:23:46,770
Because after Edmund's death,
she started acting strangely.

973
01:23:46,938 --> 01:23:49,106
She was watching me,
listening to my calls.

974
01:23:49,274 --> 01:23:51,191
That is crazy. You imagined it.

975
01:23:51,359 --> 01:23:53,485
I know. I've been
imagining things too. Plenty.

976
01:23:53,653 --> 01:23:56,447
No. No, I could tell
there was a difference.

977
01:23:56,614 --> 01:24:00,117
Maybe she knew about us.
Maybe she wants something.

978
01:24:00,285 --> 01:24:03,328
Don't you think we would have
heard from her by now?

979
01:24:03,496 --> 01:24:05,831
MATTY:
I don't know what to think.

980
01:24:06,374 --> 01:24:08,333
I'm worried, Ned.

981
01:24:09,169 --> 01:24:13,464
But it's not about the glasses
or your friends. It's us.

982
01:24:13,798 --> 01:24:17,134
Your first reaction is to accuse me.

983
01:24:17,302 --> 01:24:20,220
- What's happening to you?
- I'm sorry.

984
01:24:23,141 --> 01:24:25,142
Hardin called today.

985
01:24:25,518 --> 01:24:29,271
He said that everything should be cleared
up by next week. I'll get the money.

986
01:24:29,439 --> 01:24:31,482
He apologized for the delay.

987
01:24:32,442 --> 01:24:34,943
They've been stalling.
They're dragging it out...

988
01:24:35,111 --> 01:24:37,613
...hoping to find a way
to implicate you.

989
01:24:37,781 --> 01:24:40,074
But they haven't been able to.

990
01:24:40,784 --> 01:24:43,494
Soon, it will be all ours.

991
01:24:43,828 --> 01:24:46,830
That's why we've got to
stay together, Ned.

992
01:24:47,082 --> 01:24:48,332
It won't be long...

993
01:24:48,500 --> 01:24:52,169
...and then we can get away from here,
out from under all of this.

994
01:24:53,630 --> 01:24:56,423
All we have is each other.

995
01:24:57,759 --> 01:25:01,470
I'd kill myself if I thought
this thing would destroy us.

996
01:25:03,348 --> 01:25:05,265
I couldn't take it.

997
01:26:38,193 --> 01:26:39,693
That's great.

998
01:26:39,861 --> 01:26:42,321
- Hi, Ned.
- What are you doing here?

999
01:26:42,488 --> 01:26:45,407
I was looking for you.
Do you always run this late?

1000
01:26:45,575 --> 01:26:48,660
No. I'm going down to Miami tomorrow.
I won't have time.

1001
01:26:49,621 --> 01:26:52,539
- What's in Miami? - Closing a real
estate deal I was working on.

1002
01:26:55,960 --> 01:26:58,086
You're some kind of health nut.

1003
01:26:59,672 --> 01:27:01,798
Matty Walker smokes that same brand,
I noticed.

1004
01:27:01,966 --> 01:27:06,053
This gonna be one of those conversations?
Maybe I should have my lawyer present.

1005
01:27:06,221 --> 01:27:08,639
Buddy, your lawyer is present.

1006
01:27:18,483 --> 01:27:20,525
You know, that Edmund Walker
was a bad guy.

1007
01:27:20,693 --> 01:27:23,111
The more I find out,
the happier I am he's dead.

1008
01:27:23,279 --> 01:27:25,989
I figure it's a positive thing
for the world.

1009
01:27:26,157 --> 01:27:28,700
You're not known for being a hard-liner.

1010
01:27:28,868 --> 01:27:32,496
Well, I have my own standards.
I just try to keep them private.

1011
01:27:36,376 --> 01:27:38,919
As far as I'm concerned,
I don't care who killed him...

1012
01:27:39,087 --> 01:27:41,880
...and I don't care
who gets rich because of it.

1013
01:27:44,759 --> 01:27:48,262
But Oscar is not like that.

1014
01:27:49,222 --> 01:27:52,849
You know, his whole life is based on
doing the right thing.

1015
01:27:53,017 --> 01:27:54,768
He's the only person I know like that.

1016
01:27:54,936 --> 01:27:58,480
Sometimes, it's a real pain in the ass.
Even for him.

1017
01:28:01,901 --> 01:28:04,820
Oscar's unhappy right now.
I mean, he is in pain.

1018
01:28:05,029 --> 01:28:08,198
- Why is that?
- Because he likes you.

1019
01:28:08,741 --> 01:28:09,866
Even better than I do...

1020
01:28:10,034 --> 01:28:13,870
...that's why he's busting his butt
trying to find this Mary Ann Simpson.

1021
01:28:16,207 --> 01:28:18,166
They found her place
in Miami yesterday.

1022
01:28:18,334 --> 01:28:19,543
Yeah?

1023
01:28:19,711 --> 01:28:23,880
But the woman herself was gone.
Seems like she left in a hurry.

1024
01:28:24,966 --> 01:28:28,051
Oscar thought any story
she could tell might help.

1025
01:28:28,219 --> 01:28:30,470
He thinks you need help.

1026
01:28:31,723 --> 01:28:33,682
Oh, come on.

1027
01:28:37,103 --> 01:28:39,896
Someone is putting you
into deep trouble, my friend.

1028
01:28:41,316 --> 01:28:44,151
From 3:30 to 5 a.m.
the night Walker was killed...

1029
01:28:44,319 --> 01:28:47,237
...someone called
your hotel room repeatedly.

1030
01:28:47,405 --> 01:28:49,906
The hotel didn't wanna
put them through...

1031
01:28:50,074 --> 01:28:53,160
...but whoever it was
convinced them that it was an emergency.

1032
01:28:53,745 --> 01:28:56,872
Your phone rang and rang,
but you didn't answer.

1033
01:28:57,040 --> 01:28:59,082
- That's easy.
- Don't.

1034
01:28:59,250 --> 01:29:00,375
Don't say anything.

1035
01:29:00,585 --> 01:29:03,086
Just save it for some other time.

1036
01:29:04,589 --> 01:29:06,173
It gets worse.

1037
01:29:10,345 --> 01:29:14,097
Now someone's trying
to give us Edmund's glasses.

1038
01:29:17,185 --> 01:29:21,813
We don't know who and we don't know
what the glasses will tell us...

1039
01:29:22,732 --> 01:29:25,817
...but our negotiations are continuing.

1040
01:29:35,244 --> 01:29:38,663
I wish I knew what to tell you, Ned,
but I don't have any good ideas.

1041
01:29:48,466 --> 01:29:50,092
I'll see you.

1042
01:30:27,130 --> 01:30:28,797
We know each other, don't we?

1043
01:30:29,006 --> 01:30:31,842
Michael Glenn, with Bashford-Hillerman.

1044
01:30:32,927 --> 01:30:34,511
Ned Racine.

1045
01:30:35,555 --> 01:30:38,140
Oh, Christ, I've done it again.

1046
01:30:38,307 --> 01:30:41,268
I'm just here waiting for some people.

1047
01:30:44,397 --> 01:30:45,814
Okay, this is silly.

1048
01:30:45,982 --> 01:30:48,942
You're not still mad
about that Gourson business?

1049
01:30:50,027 --> 01:30:51,027
We had to do it.

1050
01:30:51,195 --> 01:30:54,698
Costanza practically insisted
that we sue you.

1051
01:30:55,116 --> 01:30:57,868
Nobody at our place likes malpractice
against other lawyers.

1052
01:30:58,035 --> 01:30:59,578
Forget it.

1053
01:31:01,497 --> 01:31:04,666
Well, hey, I tried to make it up to you.

1054
01:31:06,878 --> 01:31:08,879
You ever meet a lady
named Matty Walker?

1055
01:31:09,714 --> 01:31:11,214
You'd remember her.

1056
01:31:11,382 --> 01:31:13,467
- A very hot number.
- Matty Walker.

1057
01:31:13,634 --> 01:31:15,135
Yeah, I met her at a party.

1058
01:31:15,303 --> 01:31:17,721
She said she was going up there...

1059
01:31:17,889 --> 01:31:20,474
...and wanted to know about lawyers.

1060
01:31:21,517 --> 01:31:23,894
- So I gave her your name. Oh, boy.
- When was this?

1061
01:31:24,061 --> 01:31:27,689
I don't know. A long time.
Maybe last year sometime.

1062
01:31:27,857 --> 01:31:30,484
- I gotta get going.
- You tell her about the Gourson case?

1063
01:31:31,527 --> 01:31:34,654
Hey, pal, I was trying to get you work.

1064
01:31:35,239 --> 01:31:36,573
Jesus. Are you nuts?

1065
01:31:36,741 --> 01:31:38,909
Did you tell her about Gourson?

1066
01:31:39,076 --> 01:31:42,454
Maybe I told her how we met.
Yeah, maybe.

1067
01:32:10,399 --> 01:32:13,151
BEVERLY:
Is something wrong with your phone?

1068
01:32:14,278 --> 01:32:16,446
It's just off the hook. Why?

1069
01:32:17,031 --> 01:32:20,158
Teddy Lewis is in County.
He's very anxious to talk to you.

1070
01:32:23,704 --> 01:32:27,666
I don't know. It's a thing in Lauderdale,
but they're not telling me.

1071
01:32:29,418 --> 01:32:31,461
- I'm a little worried.
- I'll find out.

1072
01:32:32,213 --> 01:32:34,339
No, that's not why I called you.

1073
01:32:34,507 --> 01:32:36,466
In fact, I got me another lawyer.

1074
01:32:40,763 --> 01:32:42,681
I think it would be better.

1075
01:32:43,307 --> 01:32:48,728
- You know Schlisgal?
- Yeah, he's good.

1076
01:32:52,817 --> 01:32:57,153
This broad came to me last week.
A real looker.

1077
01:32:57,321 --> 01:33:00,156
She said that you told her
how she could reach me...

1078
01:33:00,324 --> 01:33:03,827
...and I figured that you must have
because she knew all about it.

1079
01:33:03,995 --> 01:33:06,329
She said that you wanted another one.

1080
01:33:09,792 --> 01:33:14,170
She had me show her how to
rig it to a door with a little delay.

1081
01:33:14,338 --> 01:33:16,840
Does any of this mean anything to you?

1082
01:33:19,260 --> 01:33:22,470
Then I'm glad I told you.
You better watch your step.

1083
01:33:24,348 --> 01:33:26,266
Thanks, Teddy.

1084
01:33:28,311 --> 01:33:31,271
Racine, man, don't thank me yet...

1085
01:33:32,273 --> 01:33:35,483
...because these guys have been
asking me about The Breakers.

1086
01:33:38,362 --> 01:33:42,866
Hey, I ain't told them shit,
but I don't like the look on their faces.

1087
01:33:44,869 --> 01:33:47,370
[LINE RINGING]

1088
01:34:29,580 --> 01:34:31,665
[PHONE RINGS]

1089
01:34:32,917 --> 01:34:35,085
Mr. Racine's office.

1090
01:34:36,921 --> 01:34:40,090
Ned, Mrs. Walker. Do you want her?

1091
01:34:42,051 --> 01:34:43,468
Yeah.

1092
01:34:58,609 --> 01:35:02,445
- Hello.
MATTY: Hello, Ned. Can we talk?

1093
01:35:03,989 --> 01:35:05,573
Okay.

1094
01:35:06,492 --> 01:35:08,743
- Where are you?
- I'm in Miami.

1095
01:35:08,953 --> 01:35:12,414
I've been running around like crazy
and I couldn't reach you before I left.

1096
01:35:12,581 --> 01:35:15,458
Ned, everything is gonna be all right.

1097
01:35:16,043 --> 01:35:18,128
- Tell me.
- I've got the money.

1098
01:35:18,295 --> 01:35:22,674
I've taken it and sent it somewhere safe.
It's all ours now.

1099
01:35:23,426 --> 01:35:26,136
- But that's not the best part.
- What's the best part?

1100
01:35:26,303 --> 01:35:28,680
The glasses. I got them back.

1101
01:35:28,848 --> 01:35:31,307
That is, they should be ours by now.
Betty had them.

1102
01:35:31,475 --> 01:35:34,310
She wanted money.
That's why I had to come down here.

1103
01:35:34,478 --> 01:35:37,731
She made it all very difficult,
but I think it worked out.

1104
01:35:38,023 --> 01:35:41,151
- Do you have them?
- No. She wouldn't do that.

1105
01:35:41,318 --> 01:35:43,027
She's putting them in the boathouse.

1106
01:35:43,195 --> 01:35:45,530
In the top drawer
of the dresser in the boathouse.

1107
01:35:45,740 --> 01:35:48,658
They should be there now
if she's kept up her end.

1108
01:35:49,869 --> 01:35:50,952
Yeah.

1109
01:35:51,120 --> 01:35:54,873
I think you'd better get them right away.
I don't trust her.

1110
01:35:56,333 --> 01:35:58,710
- In the boathouse?
- That's right.

1111
01:35:58,878 --> 01:36:01,087
The top drawer of the dresser.

1112
01:36:01,255 --> 01:36:03,840
Oh, Ned, we're gonna be all right.

1113
01:36:04,008 --> 01:36:08,511
I'll leave here as soon as I can.
I should be there by 7:30.

1114
01:36:08,679 --> 01:36:12,474
I can't wait to see you, darling.
We've made it.

1115
01:36:14,477 --> 01:36:18,021
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

1116
01:36:19,106 --> 01:36:20,982
Goodbye, sweetheart.

1117
01:38:03,627 --> 01:38:05,169
I better go get him.

1118
01:40:36,613 --> 01:40:40,074
- Hello, darling.
- Hello, Matty.

1119
01:40:41,785 --> 01:40:45,288
- Where's your car?
- It's out back with yours.

1120
01:40:45,748 --> 01:40:49,042
- Why didn't you turn the lights on?
- I could see.

1121
01:40:52,296 --> 01:40:54,255
It's all ours now.

1122
01:40:56,508 --> 01:40:58,843
We could leave tonight if we wanted to.

1123
01:41:00,721 --> 01:41:03,473
- It's all over.
- Yes, it is.

1124
01:41:05,184 --> 01:41:06,976
Ned, what is that?

1125
01:41:07,144 --> 01:41:09,520
It's Edmund's gun.
You remember it, don't you?

1126
01:41:10,147 --> 01:41:11,189
What's happened?

1127
01:41:12,024 --> 01:41:14,609
- I think you know.
- No, I swear I don't.

1128
01:41:14,777 --> 01:41:16,402
It's the glasses, Matty.

1129
01:41:16,987 --> 01:41:20,615
Weren't they there?
Didn't she bring them?

1130
01:41:21,200 --> 01:41:23,076
I didn't see them.

1131
01:41:23,994 --> 01:41:26,204
She promised me she would bring them.

1132
01:41:26,371 --> 01:41:30,666
Maybe I missed them.
The way you missed them that night.

1133
01:41:31,293 --> 01:41:34,045
Ned, I don't know what you're thinking,
but you're wrong.

1134
01:41:34,338 --> 01:41:35,922
I'd never do anything to hurt you.

1135
01:41:36,381 --> 01:41:40,343
- I love you, you've got to believe that.
- Keep talking, Matty.

1136
01:41:40,511 --> 01:41:43,930
Experience shows
I can be convinced of anything.

1137
01:41:50,312 --> 01:41:53,648
I did arrange to meet you, Ned,
but that all changed.

1138
01:41:53,816 --> 01:41:58,569
You changed it. I fell in love with you.
I didn't plan that.

1139
01:41:58,737 --> 01:42:01,739
You never quit, do you?
You just keep on coming.

1140
01:42:01,907 --> 01:42:04,700
How can I prove it to you?
What can I say?

1141
01:42:04,868 --> 01:42:08,454
The glasses, Matty.
Why don't you go down there...

1142
01:42:09,081 --> 01:42:10,706
...and get them?

1143
01:42:11,291 --> 01:42:13,334
You said they weren't there.

1144
01:42:13,502 --> 01:42:16,462
I said I didn't see them.

1145
01:42:33,355 --> 01:42:35,273
I'll go, Ned.

1146
01:42:36,692 --> 01:42:38,693
I'll go and look for them.

1147
01:42:52,291 --> 01:42:56,669
Ned, no matter what you think...

1148
01:42:57,629 --> 01:42:59,672
...I do love you.

1149
01:43:19,776 --> 01:43:20,943
No.

1150
01:43:23,238 --> 01:43:24,864
Matty!

1151
01:44:07,908 --> 01:44:09,867
She's alive.

1152
01:44:14,122 --> 01:44:16,666
They found the body in the boathouse.

1153
01:44:17,376 --> 01:44:20,002
What if that was
somebody else's body in the boathouse?

1154
01:44:20,170 --> 01:44:24,048
What if it was already there
when I got there, dead and waiting for me?

1155
01:44:24,216 --> 01:44:27,051
Maybe her friend, Mary Ann.

1156
01:44:27,511 --> 01:44:30,471
Her teeth were left, man.

1157
01:44:31,098 --> 01:44:35,059
They were sent back to Illinois.
The identification was positive.

1158
01:44:35,602 --> 01:44:37,353
That was her.

1159
01:44:37,771 --> 01:44:40,898
That was Matty Tyler Walker.

1160
01:44:41,066 --> 01:44:44,193
That was her and she is dead.

1161
01:44:44,361 --> 01:44:47,446
You are not listening to me.

1162
01:44:48,490 --> 01:44:52,118
Maybe she was using
this other girl's name...

1163
01:44:52,286 --> 01:44:55,079
...since she first met Walker
three years ago...

1164
01:44:55,247 --> 01:44:59,250
...since she first spotted him and decided
to take him one way or the other.

1165
01:44:59,668 --> 01:45:01,294
Maybe...

1166
01:45:01,878 --> 01:45:06,132
...Walker, or any of us,
never knew her real name.

1167
01:45:06,300 --> 01:45:08,551
Why would she want to hide
her identity?

1168
01:45:08,719 --> 01:45:10,553
I don't know.

1169
01:45:10,721 --> 01:45:14,015
Maybe because there was something
in her past, something so bad...

1170
01:45:14,182 --> 01:45:16,767
...that it would queer it with Walker
if he found out...

1171
01:45:16,935 --> 01:45:19,061
...that he'd never marry her.

1172
01:45:24,526 --> 01:45:25,901
Let's say...

1173
01:45:26,069 --> 01:45:31,073
...that she's living as this other girl,
this person from her past.

1174
01:45:32,200 --> 01:45:34,910
So there's only one person
in the whole world...

1175
01:45:35,078 --> 01:45:37,872
...who knows who she really is.

1176
01:45:38,206 --> 01:45:41,250
And then, just when she's got me
on the line...

1177
01:45:42,127 --> 01:45:46,255
...she's finally going to collect,
that person shows up.

1178
01:45:46,423 --> 01:45:50,092
That girl finds her
and threatens to expose her...

1179
01:45:50,260 --> 01:45:52,970
...so Matty starts paying her off.

1180
01:45:53,138 --> 01:45:56,265
Maybe she even promised to cut her in
on Edmund's money.

1181
01:45:58,101 --> 01:46:01,604
Now she's got to share it
with two people.

1182
01:46:03,440 --> 01:46:05,733
But then, Matty sees a way...

1183
01:46:05,901 --> 01:46:09,278
...to get rid of both of us at once.

1184
01:46:12,115 --> 01:46:14,075
At the boathouse.

1185
01:46:15,786 --> 01:46:18,996
A way to solve all her problems...

1186
01:46:19,206 --> 01:46:22,958
...and get clear
with no one looking for her.

1187
01:46:24,503 --> 01:46:29,298
She was right too, because I would have
never stopped looking for her.

1188
01:46:32,302 --> 01:46:34,428
Matty killed this other girl...

1189
01:46:34,638 --> 01:46:38,057
...and put her body in the boathouse.

1190
01:46:38,433 --> 01:46:40,142
It was so...

1191
01:46:40,644 --> 01:46:43,270
...perfect. It was so...

1192
01:46:44,356 --> 01:46:46,482
...clean.

1193
01:46:47,692 --> 01:46:51,654
You find two bodies,
me and this girl...

1194
01:46:51,822 --> 01:46:54,657
...two killers, dead.

1195
01:46:54,950 --> 01:46:56,659
Case closed.

1196
01:46:58,036 --> 01:47:01,747
You can't find the money, can you, Oscar?
Doesn't that tell you something?

1197
01:47:01,957 --> 01:47:06,168
It tells me she moved it and we can't
find it, and that don't mean shit.

1198
01:47:07,170 --> 01:47:10,423
It could be sitting in a bank
anywhere in the world...

1199
01:47:10,590 --> 01:47:14,844
...waiting for some dead lady
to come for it.

1200
01:47:18,140 --> 01:47:20,516
Do you hear what you're saying?
It's crazy.

1201
